## MCP SERVER USAGE

MCP servers give the agent live access to external systems. Use them when the task requires real data — not mock or hardcoded values.

### Connected servers

| Server          | URL                                  | Use for                                          |
|-----------------|--------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Gmail           | `https://gmail.mcp.claude.com/mcp`   | Read/send emails, search threads, parse content  |
| Google Calendar | `https://gcal.mcp.claude.com/mcp`    | Read events, schedule, check availability        |
| Gamma           | `https://mcp.gamma.app/mcp`          | Generate or update presentations via Gamma       |

### MCP call discipline
- Call MCP only when live data is required for the task
- Parse `mcp_tool_result` blocks by type, not by position (order is not guaranteed)
- If a call fails with auth/credential error, stop and surface it — don't retry blindly
- Combine MCP + code only when the result needs transformation (e.g., fetch calendar → generate report)

